title: Deedeemensional/Dial M for Monkey: Magmanamus/Maternal Combat
description: In "Deedeemensional", Dee Dee time-travels to save Dexter from a monster. In "Magmanamus", Monkey goes up against a lava being that dislikes human-caused noise. In "Maternal Combat", when his mother falls, Dexter creates a robot mom to substitute for her.

title: Dexter Dodgeball/Dial M for Monkey: Rasslor/Dexter's Assistant
description: After repeated pummeling in the Gym class dodgeball game, Dexter arrives for class ready for action encased in an Armored Cyber-Sonic Exo-Jock Jumpsuit.

title: Dexter's Rival/Dial M for Monkey: Simion/Old Man Dexter
description: In "Dexter's Rival", Dexter clearly shows disdain for a new kid in school, who has a lab just like his, albeit a bigger and more superior one. In "Simion", the result of an failed experiment vows revenge against the humans that did it. In "Old Man Dexter", Dexter makes himself older so he can stay up later.

title: Double Trouble/Dial M for Monkey: Barbequor/Dexter's Laboratory
description: Dexter and his cloning machine overheat when Dee Dee and her friends clone and re-clone themselves for Laboratory fun-time.

title: Jurassic Pooch/Dial M for Monkey: Orgon Grindor/Dimwit Dexter
description: After regenerating a Tyrannosaurus Rex using some puppy-dog DNA, Dexter must recapture the dinosaur-doggie beast when Dee Dee decides to take it for a walk in the park.

title: Dee Dee's Room/Dial M for Monkey: Huntor/The Big Sister
description: In "Dee Dee's Room", Dexter loses something of his and must go into Dee Dee's room to retrieve it. In "Huntor", Monkey finds himself stalked by an alien hunter. In "The Big Sister", Dee Dee eats one of Dexter's experimental cookies and becomes a giant.

title: Star Spangled Sidekicks/The Justice Friends: TV Super Pals/Game Over
description: Dexter and Dee Dee audition to be Major Glory's sidekick; The Infragable Krunk wants to watch his favorite TV show; Dexter is trapped inside a video game.

title: Babysitter Blues/The Justice Friends: Valhallen's Room/Dream Machine
description: Dexter is in love with his babysitter, Lisa.

title: Dollhouse Drama/The Justice Friends: Krunk's Date/The Big Cheese
description: Spying through Dee Dee's bedroom keyhole, Dexter thinks she is plotting against him.

title: Way of the Dee Dee/The Justice Friends: Say Uncle Sam/Tribe Called Girl
description: When Dee Dee accuses Dexter of not knowing how to live in the outside world - and only in his lab, he asks her to show him the Dee Dee way of knowledge.

title: Spacecase/The Justice Friends: Ratman/Dexter's Debt
description: In "Space Case", Dexter hands off Dee Dee to invading aliens, only to become so overcome with guilt that he decides to save her. In "Ratman", the Justice Friends discover that a vigilante raised by rats has been living in their basement the whole time. In "Dexter's Debt", Dexter owes a huge debt to NASA and must find some way to pay it.

title: Dexter's Rival/The Justice Friends: Bee Where?/Mandarker
description: The new kid in school, Mandark, steals Dexter's spotlight and his ego when he find Mandark has a bigger and better laboratory.

title: Inflata Dee Dee/The Justice Friends: Can't Nap/Monstory
description: Dee Dee dances into Dexter's Laboratory, puts on Dexter's inflatable suit, floats up above him and taunts him.

title: Beard to Be Feared/Quackor the Fowl/Ant Pants
description: Dexter decides to emulate his hero, Action Hank, and grow a synthetic beard to make himself more rugged.

title: Mom and Jerry/Chubby Cheese/That Crazy Robot
description: When Dexter's brain transplant experiment goes awry, his brain is switched with that of a mouse.

title: D & DD/Hamhocks and Armlocks
Hunger Strikes/The Koos Is Loose/Morning Stretch
description: Dexter is denied dessert when he doesn't finish his vegetables. He decides to use gamma radiation to alter his tastebuds.

title: Dee Dee Locks and the Ness Monster/Backfire/Book 'Em
description: Dexter tries to entertain his ill sister by reading to her out of his science text. Bored by protons and neutrons, Dee Dee uses her imagination to make up a story of her own.

title: Sister's Got a Brand New Bag/Shoo, Shoe Gnomes/Lab of the Lost
description: Dee Dee sees Big Daddy Fat doing a new dance on "Groove Train" and has to learn it.

title: Labels/Game Show/Fantastic Boyage
description: During a fight with his sister over the chair in front of the TV, Dexter gets the idea to start labeling his things.

title: Filet of Soul/Golden Diskette
description: "Filet of Soul": Dexter and Dee Dee are haunted by the ghost of a dead goldfish. "Golden Diskette": Dexter obsessed with finding a golden diskette to get a unprecedented tour of an eccentric inventor's mysterious factory.

title: Snowdown/*Figure Not Included/Mock 5
description: Dee Dee keeps pelting Dexter with snowballs.

title: Ewww That's Growth/Nuclear Confusion/Germ Warfare
description: When the whole family goes to the carnival, Dexter can't go on a ride because he's too short. Using his lab, he makes himself grow taller, but can't stop.

title: A Hard Day's Day/Road Rash/Ocean Commotion
description: In "A HARD DAY'S DAY", every day is a fine day for science until things take a turn for the worse thanks to the position of the stars in the sky. In "ROAD RASH", Dexter's mom forces Dexter to go outside and ride a bike, with Dee Dee challenging him to catch her on her roller blades, resulting in a chase similar to one between Wile E. Coyote and the Road Runner. In "OCEAN COMMOTION", on a visit to the beach, Dee Dee (dressed in a mermaid bathing suit) gets kidnapped by some manic seafarin' sailors and Dexter vows to save her.

roles.char: Dee Dee imitating the Road Runner

title: The Bus Boy/The Justice Friends: Things That Go Bonk in the Night/Ol' McDexter
description: When Dexter is harassed by two bullies and forced to go into the back of a school bus chasing his #2 writing implement, he must brave the legend of little Billy Blumberg who disappeared back there years ago.

title: Sassy Come Home/Photo Finish
description: While vacationing in the woods with his family, Dexter finds Sasquatch tracks and hopes to photograph the mythical beast.

title: Star Check Unconventional/Dexter Is Dirty/Ice Cream Scream
description: In "STAR CHECK UNCONVENTIONAL", Dexter and two friends are on their way to the Star Check convention, only to not wind up exactly where they wanted. In "DEXTER IS DIRTY", Dexter will do anything to avoid bathing forever... even laminate himself. In "ICE CREAM SCREAM", Dexter tries to get the ice cream vendor to stop to allow him to get some ice cream, but the vendor isn't too keen on doing that.

title: Decode of Honor/World's Greatest Mom/Ultrajerk 2000
description: When Dexter and Dee Dee get their Action Hank and Pony Puffs decoder rings mixed up (respectively), each goes through the other's initiation.

title: Techno Turtle/Surprise!/Got Your Goat
description: When Dee Dee rescues a wounded turtle from a hawk's talons, Dexter helps rebuild the little shelled animal into a bionic powerhouse.

title: Dee Dee Be Deep/911/Down in the Dumps
description: Dee Dee wants to join the choir, but her bad singing is making it impossible for Dexter to work.

title: Unfortunate Cookie/The Muffin King
description: Dexter and Dee Dee get stuck together by a Chinese Finger Puzzle, they track it to its maker in Chinatown, USA.

title: Picture Day/Now That's a Stretch/Dexter Detention
description: It's picture day at school and Dexter must face the truth: he is not photogenic. Using Dee Dee's Teen magazine as a guide for restructuring his physical appearance, Dexter becomes grotesquely handsome.

title: Don't Be a Baby/Dial M for Monkey: Peltra/G.I.R.L. Squad
description: Being too young to watch an R-rated movie, Dexter tries to make Dee Dee and himself older than Mom and Dad.

title: Sports-a-Poppin'/Koos a la Goop a Goop/Project Dee Dee
description: "Dad tries to teach Dexter a sport, like all the other fathers and sons. But Dexter is just horrible at every sport - from baseball to football, soccer to badminton, Dexter stinks!

title: Topped Off/Dee Dee's Tail/No Power Trip
description: When Dexter has to have a "parent-principal" meeting at school, the boy genius is distraught. He's never been in trouble so how can he disappoint his parents now?

title: Sister Mom/The Laughing
description: "Sister Mom": Dexter is so worried about something bad he did at school that, when his mother is called on it, he has Dee Dee turned into their mother instead. "The Laughing": Dexter is accidentally bitten by a clown and turns into one himself at night.

title: Dexter's Lab: A Story/Coupon for Craziness/Better Off Wet
description: When Dexter takes in a lost Labrador Retriever, he decides to enable the dog to talk.

title: Critical Gas/Let's Save the World You Jerk!/Average Joe
description: Dexter wolfs down a burrito and suddenly feels a growing pain inside. After having his computer analyze the pain, Dexter thinks he's going to explode.

title: Rushmore Rumble/A Boy and His Bug/You Vegetabelieve It!
description: Mandark and Dexter battle each other with Rushmore Presidents Washington and Lincoln brought to life. / Dexter has a metal eating termite named Timmy as a pet. / Dee Dee uses way too much of Dexter's super growth formula in the backyard and turns the plants into man eating monsters.

title: Aye Aye Eyes/Dee Dee and the Man
description: When Dexter returns a little girl's stuffed bunny to her, she falls in love with him. She is soon stalking Dexter. With the help of Dee Dee, Dexter is eventually able to divert the girl's affections toward another little boy.

title: Old Flame/Don't Be a Hero/My Favorite Martian
description: Dexter wants to meet the original genius who invented fire and zips back in time. He grabs the unsuspecting and frightened caveman and brings him back to the lab.

title: Paper Route Bout/The Old Switcharooms/Trick or Treehouse
description: 'Paper Route Bout": Dee Dee starts a paper route, but finds herself up against some ninjas. "The Old Switcharooms': after they destroy their father's bowling trophy, he sends Dexter and Dee Dee to each other's rooms. 'Trick or Treehouse': Dee Dee builds herself a treehouse and Dexter is anxious to know what's going on.

title: Quiet Riot/Accent You Hate/Catch of the Day
description: When a bully who hates kids with funny accents sets his sights on Dexter, the boy genius has until 3:00 before he receives an after-school beating.

title: Dad Is Disturbed/Framed/That's Using Your Head
DiM/Just an Old Fashioned Lab Song.../Repairanoid
description: While Dexter is working in his lab, one of the light bulbs burns out. Mom takes him to a giant hardware store in an exhausting journey to replace it.

title: Sdrawkcab/The Continuum of Cartoon Fools/Sun, Surf, and Science
description: Dexter develops a reverse belt. While wearing the belt to get a snack in the kitchen, Dee Dee sneaks into the lab to play with the belt controls.

title: Big Bots/Gooey Aliens That Control Your Mind/Misplaced in Space
description: Dexter builds Dee Dee a huge robot after she tells him he can't. The problem begins when they use their robots to try to save a volcanic island from eruption.

title: Dee Dee's Rival/Pslyghtly Psycho/Game for a Game
description: In an episode that mirrors "Dexter's Rival," Dee Dee goes head to head with the new student in her dance class, Olga - Mandark's sister.

title: Blackfoot and Slim/Trapped with a Vengeance/The Parrot Trap
description: Dexter and Dee Dee are unknowingly the focus of a "Wild Kingdom" type animal documentary. During Dexter's bathing ritual, he realizes he's being observed, runs, gets tranquilized, and upon awakening discovers he's been tagged.

title: Dexter and Computress Get Mandark!/The Justice Friends: Pain in the Mouth/Dexter vs. Santa's Claws
description: Dee Dee uses the lab computer to send her wish list to Santa Claus, but Dexter mocks her because he doesn't believe in the Santa.

title: Dyno-Might/LABretto
description: Through opera we see Dexter's origins leading up to the creation of his laboratory.

title: Last But Not Beast
description: In Japan as part of a student exchange program, Dexter gets involved in a battle.

title: Streaky Clean/A Dad Cartoon/Sole Brother
description: "Streaky Clean" (9 minutes) When Dexter gets tired of spilling stuff on himself, he invents a washing machine satellite to zap out any spots. But when the satellite is nudged in space to a higher setting, the spots aren't the only things that get removed.

title: Mind Over Chatter/A Quakor Cartoon/Momdark
description: "Mind Over Chatter" (9 minutes) Dexter wants to know what Dad has gotten him for his birthday, so he creates an invention so he can read minds. But when it backfires, it's everyone else who can read Dexter's thoughts.

title: Copping an Aptitude/A Failed Lab Experiment/The Grand-Daddy of All Inventions
description: "Copping an Attitude" (9 minutes) Dexter goes to college ready to learn only to discover it's party central. But when Dexter fries out by over-studying, he's ready to party and creates the biggest party ever.

title: Poppa Wheely/A Mom Cartoon/The Mock Side of the Moon
description: "Poppa Wheelie" - Dexter's school has Career Day, "A Mom Cartoon" - Mom is shopping and suddenly a sale is announced. "Mockside of the Moon" - Dexter discovers that the moon is hallow and monsters are living inside.

title: If Memory Serves/A Mandark Cartoon/Tele Trauma
description: "If Memory Serves" (9 minutes) Dexter sees that his parents are forgetting things and creates a device to download his memories before they are lost. But when Mandark shows up to steal memories, it's an all-out fight to keep Dexter's genius safe.

title: A Boy Named Sue/Lab on the Run
description: "Boy Named Sue" (11 minutes) Mandark reveals the origin of his anger is from being named Susan and being raised by New Age parents who disallowed science. This comes to a head when he meets Dexter, a science genius, who disregards Susan as not being scientifically equal.

title: Dos Boot/A Dee Dee Cartoon/Would You Like That in the Can
description: "Dos Boot" (9 minutes) When Mandark downloads himself into Dexter's computer, Dexter must upload himself in order to combat this virus.

title: That Magic Moment/A Silent Cartoon/Opposites Attract
description: "That Magic Moment" (9 minutes) Uncle Magic comes to visit the family and promises to make Dee Dee disappear in a trick. Dexter poo-poos his Uncle's world of illusion and makes Dee Dee disappear via science.

title: Comic Relief/A Third Dad Cartoon/Robo Dexo 3000
description: "Comic Relief" (9 minutes) When reading his latest comic book adventure isn't enough for Dexter, he makes a machine so he can create his own adventure. Dexter enters this comic book world and becomes a comic book hero himself-complete with his own supervillain to battle.

title: Glove at First Sight/A Mom & Dad Cartoon/Smells Like Victory
description: "Glove At First Sight" (9 minutes) It's a flashback to the 80s as Mom deals with her germaphobia with the slob that will someday be her true love.

title: Oh, Brother/Another Dad Cartoon/Bar Exam
description: "Oh Brother" (9 minutes) Dexter is convinced that life would be better if he had an older brother. But he soon learns Dee Dee wasn't really that bad.

title: Jeepers, Creepers, Where Is Peepers?/Go, Dexter Family, Go!
description: "Jeepers, Creepers, Where is Peepers" (11 minutes) Koosie's dog Peepers is stolen from Koosland. Koosie begs Dexter for help and Dexter must balance his world of science with Koosie's land of imagination.

title: Scare Tactics/A Mom Cartoon/My Dad vs. Your Dad
description: "Scare Tactics" (9 minutes) When Dad won't let Dexter stay up for a late-night scary movie, Dexter sneaks down and watches anyway. Dad sees this and tries to scare Dexter. But then his own trick backfires as the two of them end up being scared by all the spooky sounds in the house.

title: Beau Tie/Remember Me?/Over-Labbing
description: "Beau tie" (7 minutes) Dee Dee brings home a boy who's not only cute-he's smart. Soon Dexter and Dee Dee are fighting for his attention.

title: Sis-Tem Error/Bad Cable Manners/Dexter's Library
description: "Sis-tem Error" (7 minutes) Dee Dee accidentally shuts down the lab and must embody all of Dexter's lab so he doesn't find out.

title: The Scrying Game/Monstrosi-Dee Dee/Dad Man Walking
description: "The Scrying Game" (7 minutes) Dee Dee reads Dexter's fortune and, much to his shock, the things she predicted actually start happening.

title: Dexter's Little Dilemma/Faux Chapeau/D2
description: "Dexter's Little Dilemma" (7 minutes) Dexter has shrunk his parents and put them in a model of the house. But the house isn't complete, so Dexter must scramble about before they discover the truth.

title: Head Band/Stuffed Animal House/Used Ink
description: "Head Band" (7 minutes) Dee Dee has a song stuck in her head-literally. Dexter discovers that Dee Dee has a viral boy band infecting her brain and must come up with a cure before it spreads throughout the world.

title: School Girl Crushed/Chess Mom/Father Knows Least
description: "School Girl Crushed" (7 minutes) Dexter and Mandark attempt to defend their scientific turfs when a new scientific genius come to town. The only thing different is that this genius is a girl!

title: Dexter the Barbarian/Tuber Time/Sore Eyes
description: "Dexter the Barbarian" (7 minutes) Dexter is a barbarian just trying to make his way to the bathroom.

title: Babe Sitter/Mountain Mandark/2Geniuses 2Gether 4Ever
Height Unseen/Bygone Errors/Folly Calls
description: "Height Unseen" (7 minutes) When everyone but him has had a growth spurt, Dexter decides to try and make himself tall. When that fails, he switches things around, making everyone else short.

title: Voice Over/Blonde Leading the Blonde/Comic Stripper
description: "Voice Over" (7 minutes) When Computer gets laryngitis, Dexter must find a replacement voice for her.

title: The Lab of Tomorrow/Chicken Scratch/Garage Sale
description: "The Lab of Tomorrow" (7 minutes) Dexter narrates as he shows new scientists the great inventions he has planned for a super, future, modern lab.

title: Tee Party/Dexter's Wacky Races
description: "Tee Party" (11 minutes) When Dad makes Dexter be his caddy, Dexter destroys the normally peaceful game of golf.

title: They Got Chops/Poetic Injustice/Comedy of Feathers
description: "They Got Chops" (7 minutes) When Dee Dee starts layin' the judo on Dexter, he learns to fight back.

title: Rude Removal
description: When Dexter creates a new invention to get DeeDee's rudeness under control, her foolish antics cause both her and Dexter to end up in the machine, resulting in them becoming polite, and their rude, evil counterparts being made. Now, the polite Dexter and DeeDee must find a way to rid of the disrespectful clones of themselves before they cause even more trouble.
